ior management and a mentor and to further develop their own leadership skills can i get financial support to pay for an mba level salary many nonprofit government and social purpose for profit organizations have summer employment opportunities for graduate students yet find it difficult to pay mba level salaries you may apply for supplemental funding from the stanford management internship fund smif smif selection criteria the smif selection process is rigorous both for organizations that wish to hire a stanford mba student and for students interested in participating organizations must involve their smif fellow in a mission critical project and mentor the fellow throughout the summer students must demonstrate preparedness for the experience and a commitment to making real impact as a summer employee smif conditions and eligibility fellowships are granted for ten to twelve weeks students are eligible only if they return to the gsb after their smif fellowship the following organizations are eligible for smif support 501 c 3 nonprofit organizations or equivalent if non us public entities such as government agencies selected social purpose for profit businesses contact us for more details you are missing some flash content that should appear here perhaps your browser cannot display it or maybe it did not initialize correctly calendar jan may internship recruiting season smif fellowship applications accepted in three rounds feb 13 april 10 may 8 contact us for more information contact us related links smif employer guide smif employer application to be completed with your selected gsb intern post an internship position on the gsb recruiter dashboard admissions faculty & research alumni recruiters & companies giving executive education news about the gsb copyright 2009 stanford graduate school of business site help terms of use & policies stanford university
